strings.Value: "After I walk through this door, I hope to never see you again, crow."
"I've changed my mind. I have other matters to attend to first."

{n}The raven's gleeful caws echo off the walls.{/n}"You came, {race}! Past the ancient gate, thrrrrough the {g|Valley of the Dead}Valley of the Dead{/g}... you've struck down all who stood in your path! Despite the danger awaiting you, you still came! My masterrr knew you'd be a worrrthy serrrvant!"

"One morrre step, {race} — the sanctuarrry of my masterrr lies beyond! Accept yourrr fate without fearrr — and Vordakai will be merrrciful! But rremember — once you open the doorrr beforrre you, therrre's no turning back!"
"So, the cowardice of your kind overrrcame you afterrr all, {race}! Go on, rrrun! Rrrun frrrom one you cannot hope to escape!"
"Don't waste yourrr brrreath on foolish jests — my masterrr doesn't like to wait, and you've been trrrying his patience long enough!"
"Go forrrth, {race}! May yourrr death be intertwined with the ecstasy of sufferrring neverrrending!"
